reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So many shoes!
reviews.reviewText: This thing is amazing! It holds all of the shoes for my family of 6. Very sturdy when it is loaded with shoes, too. It was easy to put together. We keep it on our screened in porch and it’s not a total eyesore. I also love that it came with some hooks so I can hang pet leashes, hats, keys, etc. from them for quick reaching.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to Assemble
reviews.reviewText: I am extremely happy with this purchase. I was able to assemble this pretty quickly with my 4 year old who insisted on helping. We are a family of 3 and it fits all our shoes including bookbags/purses. The hooks on the side are great for keys and winter things like hats and scarves. Overall the unit is pretty solid and not wobbly. Seriously thinking of purchasing another one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Its nice but…
reviews.reviewText: It fits a descent amount of shoes, and easy to assemble but its quite flimsy being the connectors are plastic. It works with the weight of the shoes as long as it can rest against the walls! And the metal bars bend very easily!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very sturdy and holds a lot
reviews.reviewText: Really love this shelf. I have a large shoe collection and this holds almost all of them! I have upwards of 60 pairs of shoes and this shelf holds almost all of them! I use the smaller, outside sections for shoes, then the taller inner sections for clothes. This has been a huge help in a smaller space. I use the little hooks/hangers on the ends for bras. This is really a great space saver and it holds a ton!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Assembly is lengthy
reviews.reviewText: I am pretty familiar with assembling furniture, and while the process wasn't complicated, it did take me a long time to get everything together. One of its perks is you can easily customize the set up to suit what you're looking for - in my case, I needed A LOT of boot spaces. Instead of installing all 4 bars for each row, I only installed the back two and can fit everything I need to. As a result, I did have some left over pieces (of course), but I just tossed them. It was pretty easy to move (despite the bulk) when the rack was empty, and once the shoes are on seems sturdy enough. Haven't had any issues so far. None of the parts came in damaged, as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Because I configured this rack to suit my personal needs, I had a few pieces of the tubing left over; however, the shelves went together very quickly. They fit together nicely, and I LOVED the ability to adjust each shelf to the height I needed. Once it was put together, it was light enough for me to set it in the "spot" I'd chosen for it to occupy. All in all, I'm very pleased with this produce. It looks very sleek, yet it's efficient.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Large enough for high tops and boots!
reviews.reviewText: Daunting opening the box, but easy to put together, Took about 45min. It’s sturdy! Holds all the sneakers and shoes in the garage and it looks so nice! Gave us the push to clean out the garage.. so happy with this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Slightly deceiving image
reviews.reviewText: So the good: it is sturdy, lightweight, and easy to assemble.The not-so-good: In the image, there are several pairs of high-heel shoes featured. Looking closely, it appears that the heals are supported by more than tubular poles which is what I was hoping. The materials under the heels in the picture advertised looks much broader than a tube. Well, while the shelving system does come with six "sheets" of plastic material as pictured, each of the other shelves are 4 tubes with wide gaps in between. The back of all of my heels fall straight through and the front of each shoe sticks upward. Not helpful. I wish they would have included a sheet of the black plastic material for each shelf.If you are looking to use this for lots of high-heeled shoes like I was, look elsewhere.But if you need to store tennis shoes and a few pairs of tall boots, this could work perfectly. It really is a nice shoe storage system, it just doesn't meet my needs without more of the sheets to prevent my heels from falling through.
Took out the middle, it was to long for the area, hold all of my kids shoes. Good purchase.
Awesome, love it and was sooo easy to assemble. Came with a little hammer and fits sooo many shoes and boots. And I like that I can configure its size as well.
